WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:00.933
Hello everybody.

00:00:00.933 --> 00:00:05.599
I'm Brandon Biggs, and this is Diana Biggs, and welcome to today's broadcast.

00:00:07.200 --> 00:00:13.560
I told you all for my birthday one year, the Lord said, 'I want to give you a little present.

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:17.670
' I was in prayer, and I was just seeking Him.

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:19.991
He said, 'I want to show you something.

00:00:19.991 --> 00:00:27.554
' All of a sudden, I was interceding for my birthday, and I was seeing in the spirit.

00:00:28.051 --> 00:00:33.950
I saw these beautiful mountains with snow caps on the top of them.

00:00:33.950 --> 00:00:38.390
They looked like the Swiss Alps—absolutely beautiful mountains.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:46.736
There was a green valley with grass that was just the most beautiful, translucent-looking grass.

00:00:46.736 --> 00:00:52.091
It was gorgeous grass with flowers, like a meadow with butterflies.

00:00:52.777 --> 00:01:00.160
It was just the most beautiful backdrop with these mountains, a lake, and this beautiful scenery all around.

00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:07.194
Diana was doing cartwheels, and the Lord said, 'This is moments after the Rapture.

00:01:07.194 --> 00:01:10.604
' We were standing there in heaven.

00:01:10.604 --> 00:01:16.084
I was a young man; I looked a lot younger and I had hair.

00:01:16.084 --> 00:01:20.853
I had a glorified body, and Diana had her glorified body.

00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:23.547
She said, 'Brandon, we made it!

00:01:23.547 --> 00:01:23.822
We made it!

00:01:23.822 --> 00:01:29.640
' She was doing cartwheels, and she was just rejoicing and running through this meadow.

00:01:29.920 --> 00:01:36.183
It was green all around, with a beautiful green hill, and she was running and rejoicing.

00:01:36.526 --> 00:01:38.240
It was just so beautiful.

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:47.617
I was breathing in the beautiful atmosphere of heaven for the very first time.

00:01:49.291 --> 00:01:57.160
Whenever you get to a hotel room or go to a place on vacation where you've never been, you want to see everything and all the sights around because you're just excited to be there.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:04.960
Multiply that by a billion.

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:10.159
That's what this felt like: we made it.

00:02:10.159 --> 00:02:15.476
And the temperature—I remember I could feel it—it was like I was there.

00:02:15.869 --> 00:02:17.244
The atmosphere was about 65 to 70 degrees.

00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:23.572
It wasn't hot, but it wasn't cold.

00:02:23.572 --> 00:02:25.919
It was a perfect temperature.

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:34.080
Everything was perfect, and you could see those mountains, and it was just beautiful.

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:38.879
I want to tell you all, heaven is a real place.

00:02:39.259 --> 00:02:41.540
Most people go, 'Well, is it?

00:02:41.540 --> 00:02:43.540
' No, I've seen it.

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:45.159
I've been there.

00:02:45.159 --> 00:02:51.377
I've seen it—it is a massive, planet-like place.

00:02:56.160 --> 00:02:56.507
It is humongous.

00:02:56.507 --> 00:03:02.496
When I was taken back and I was coming to the Earth, it was in a ripple, how He had it hidden.

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:18.525
It was a massive place, like three times the size of Jupiter, and there was no darkness at all.

00:03:19.062 --> 00:03:20.415
Everything was glowing.

00:03:20.415 --> 00:03:27.599
There were no shadows because there is no darkness.

00:03:27.959 --> 00:03:30.731
How do you explain that to somebody?

00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:40.754
Because all we know are shadows—there are shadows on the table.

00:03:40.754 --> 00:03:43.360
But there, there is no darkness.

00:03:43.360 --> 00:03:45.234
Everything is beautiful.

00:03:45.628 --> 00:03:50.274
Then one day I was praying, and the Lord told me to tell you all about this.

00:03:50.525 --> 00:04:00.969
That's how that basically ended; He allowed me to see Diana doing the cartwheels, and I was just looking over the horizon at the beauty of an area of heaven.

00:04:02.704 --> 00:04:10.606
I don't know if my house was nearby there or not, but I wouldn't mind it in that green valley, by that lake, and those mountains with the snow tops.

00:04:11.200 --> 00:04:17.079
The things He has for every single one of you!

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:19.466
If you only knew how much He loves you.

00:04:19.466 --> 00:04:27.060
If you just read your Bible and look at whenever it says that God is love, God loves you.

00:04:27.575 --> 00:04:37.244
He gave His one and only begotten Son, that whosoever believes in Him should not perish but have everlasting life.

00:04:37.244 --> 00:04:43.547
Every single one of us has an opportunity today to say yes to Jesus and no to hell.

00:04:43.547 --> 00:04:45.280
Every single one of us.

00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:48.586
You have a hell to shun and a heaven to gain.

00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:53.840
Rodney Howard-Browne talks about that.

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:59.003
But I just want to encourage you all that when we go in the Rapture...

00:04:59.003 --> 00:05:04.740
I was praying one day, just like I always do.

00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:08.133
I said, 'Lord, what are you up to today?

00:05:08.133 --> 00:05:09.440
What is going on with you?

00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:10.650
'—just being personal with Him.

00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:14.900
And He said, 'Brandon, I'm going to show you what I'm doing.

00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:18.751
' He opened up a portal above me.

00:05:18.751 --> 00:05:25.150
It was a beautiful portal, and Jesus looked out through that portal and said, 'I'm going to show you what I'm doing today.

00:05:25.150 --> 00:05:28.249
' Just like that, right up here.

00:05:28.618 --> 00:05:32.1000
All of a sudden, I went into that portal in the spirit.

00:05:32.1000 --> 00:05:48.656
I went into that portal that He opened up above our living room, and I could see millions of plate settings that stretched forever, lined up on these beautiful tables.

00:06:04.016 --> 00:06:04.983
I'm talking beautiful wood tables with a gloss on them, not cheap plastic tables from Walmart.

00:06:10.551 --> 00:06:20.560
Each one of them had a name tag prepared for each one of us.

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:29.590
There was a doily in the middle, and beautiful fine china with golden lace around it.

00:06:30.850 --> 00:06:48.366
It was all specifically designed for you out of the desires of your heart—the things that you find beautiful and attractive, things where you go, 'Wow, that makes me so happy, Lord.

00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:49.509
Thank you for that.

00:06:49.509 --> 00:06:52.447
' Because God loves beautiful things.

00:06:52.447 --> 00:07:00.915
He is meticulous in everything He does; He cares about every single detail concerning every single one of you.

00:07:01.431 --> 00:07:09.268
Even your name is on that name card in the center of those plates.

00:07:09.268 --> 00:07:23.199
On my plate, what He was showing me, I saw Brandon Biggs and I saw a translucent-looking lily plate that was beautiful because I love flowers.

00:07:24.015 --> 00:07:28.822
I am a flower person; I love landscaping and flowers.

00:07:28.822 --> 00:07:34.559
I could spend hours just pulling weeds and making things look beautiful.

00:07:34.559 --> 00:07:41.886
I love flowers of all His creation—it's a big deal for me.

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:50.160
I saw that my plate was a lily, and it was pink and beautiful.

00:07:50.418 --> 00:07:57.312
Then the one next to me was white-looking china, and I saw the settings of the forks.

00:08:03.474 --> 00:08:14.160
Then there were some plates down over here that had chopsticks in them because not everybody likes to use a fork.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:14.720
That's neat!

00:08:14.720 --> 00:08:17.120
There are some people who like chopsticks.

00:08:17.120 --> 00:08:19.467
They might say, 'Well, what are we going to eat?

00:08:19.467 --> 00:08:20.160
' I don't know.

00:08:21.531 --> 00:08:23.787
The Bible says the marriage supper of the Lamb.

00:08:23.787 --> 00:08:26.020
What is that?

00:08:27.220 --> 00:08:27.520
I don't know.

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:29.588
Maybe we'll eat lamb—I have no idea, folks.

00:08:43.200 --> 00:08:43.497
I just know that there's a reception, and I saw the reception He was preparing for the bride, and it was beautiful.

00:08:46.422 --> 00:08:53.200
There was lace and beautiful things throughout the trees, and there were twinkle lights in that lace, powered by Holy Spirit power, I guess.

00:08:53.200 --> 00:09:01.760
They were like little lightning bugs all inside of this lace, and it was wrapped in tulle in these humongous oak trees, like weeping willows.

00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:12.994
You know how you see those down in New Orleans where the moss is dangling out of those trees?

00:09:12.994 --> 00:09:21.576
It was like that, but there was gorgeous-looking lace in this massive tree next to the table.

00:09:21.576 --> 00:09:22.193
Beautiful!

00:09:22.810 --> 00:09:26.959
It was a ginormous tree, not some skinny tree.

00:09:26.959 --> 00:09:30.746
I'm talking about trees with huge trunks.

00:09:32.114 --> 00:09:36.697
They were all in the atmosphere above, wrapped in tulle with little twinkle lights.

00:09:38.211 --> 00:09:39.995
I could see all of that.

00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:53.599
Then they had flower arrangements on all the tables in crystal vases—beautiful things that fanned out with all kinds of beautiful purples, greens, baby's breath, and beautiful lavender and pink flowers.

00:09:53.919 --> 00:09:55.519
It was done so perfectly.

00:09:55.519 --> 00:09:56.800
All of it.

00:09:57.120 --> 00:10:02.380
And they were on all the tables and all the doilies and all of it.

00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:09.280
It was just so like a beautiful, beautiful wedding reception.

00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:25.497
And then I don't want to cut it too short because I always try to tell y'all the things about it, and sometimes I add more to it because I'm like, you know, why hurry?

00:10:32.730 --> 00:10:33.550
Why hurry?

00:10:34.370 --> 00:10:36.596
You know, if you want to listen to it, fine.

00:10:36.596 --> 00:10:37.620
If you don't, fine.

00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:38.729
Fast forward it.

00:10:38.729 --> 00:10:46.720
But it was just beautiful, and it was, as far as I could see, plates and things ready for the people, and they were all okay.

00:10:46.720 --> 00:11:03.119
So one table setting was like this, and the table was all like an old English-looking table, like what you would see in a royal castle, like for the queen, because the table was all like it was all cut out like from a single piece of wood.

00:11:03.119 --> 00:11:06.453
It wasn't like, you know, like we make our cheap-looking tables today.

00:11:06.453 --> 00:11:13.120
We're talking it looked like Prince George, like, you know, like the old beds.

00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:18.480
It looked like the legs on that table were all kind of engraved wood.

00:11:20.279 --> 00:11:25.330
Engraved, and so you could see it, but it was a darker wood, a lighter wood, and then a darker wood.

00:11:25.330 --> 00:11:30.285
And it flushed in like it was just like marble-looking wood.

00:11:30.708 --> 00:11:32.399
And it was gorgeous.

00:11:32.399 --> 00:11:44.839
And then the Lord showed me the tables, but they went table, aisle, table, aisle, and every single person was just ready for them.

00:11:44.839 --> 00:11:47.769
And it went as far as you could see.

00:11:47.769 --> 00:11:50.586
I mean, you know, we're talking millions of people here.

00:11:50.586 --> 00:11:53.177
I don't know if it's by shift or whatever.

00:11:53.177 --> 00:11:54.903
You come by the generation.

00:11:54.903 --> 00:11:55.691
I don't know.

00:11:55.691 --> 00:11:58.853
How are you going to have the reception for all those people?

00:11:58.853 --> 00:11:59.773
But heaven's huge.

00:12:00.079 --> 00:12:06.269
But I'm just saying it just, you know, for what I could see, it was for hundreds of thousands.

00:12:06.269 --> 00:12:07.019
I don't know.

00:12:07.019 --> 00:12:13.679
I don't tell that it was millions of places for what I could see, but it was amazing.

00:12:13.679 --> 00:12:20.240
And then I could see the English Tudor houses.

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:23.669
Oh, yeah, the old cobblestone homes.

00:12:23.669 --> 00:12:32.925
And see, in that generation of people, whether it's 1700s or whatever, that was their heart's desire.

00:12:32.925 --> 00:12:39.440
The Bible says that he's making a mansion for every single one of us, and it would be our heart's desire.

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:45.313
So, your heart's desire in this modern day, your house is going to look a lot different than theirs.

00:12:45.313 --> 00:12:51.360
So if they were in the 1600s and 1500s, their heart's desire was just an English-style house.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:53.839
And it was gorgeous, but it was all perfect.

00:12:54.159 --> 00:12:57.330
The cobblestone on the side of this house was all perfect.

00:12:57.330 --> 00:13:12.453
And I could see it, and it was like going through a downtown, going through an old downtown because there were houses on both sides, and I could see the old roofs, the way they had it.

00:13:12.453 --> 00:13:24.697
And then the streets were gold, and it went up, and there was a curve, and there was grass, beautiful cut grass, perfect grass that was just like manicured like a golf course.

00:13:27.546 --> 00:13:28.133
Perfect.

00:13:28.133 --> 00:13:32.262
And they were having parade practice.

00:13:32.262 --> 00:13:35.339
And I said, "Lord, what are y'all doing?

00:13:35.339 --> 00:13:40.320
" He said, "We're getting ready for the celebration of you coming home.

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:58.903
" And I saw the banners, the royal banners of people, and it said 'King of Kings' and 'Lord of Lords' on these banners that were written out in gold letters that looked like on a royalty purple, a deep purple with golden letters.

00:13:58.903 --> 00:14:04.056
And it had beautiful tooling on the side, this beautiful like embroidery of gold.

00:14:04.056 --> 00:14:10.670
And it was purple with golden letters that said 'King of Kings' and 'Lord of Lords'.

00:14:10.670 --> 00:14:27.247
And they were standing there, and the people were standing there in their robes, and they had their heavenly garments on, all different styles of clothes, all different styles of outfits, the way they looked.

00:14:27.247 --> 00:14:39.885
Not everybody was the same, but everybody was worshiping, and they were saying, "For he is good and his mercy endures forever, for the Lord is good and his mercy endures forever.

00:14:39.885 --> 00:14:59.105
" And as he was marching down the street on the golden street, Jesus was riding his horse, and he had a crown on his head that looked like it had a white around it with this black-looking leopard stuff, and it went up in purple and gold and went up like this.

00:14:59.105 --> 00:15:10.750
And it had a thing on the top, and he had a purple-looking cloak on with a white embroidery around it, and then he had this beautiful outfit, a robe-like, gown-looking thing, and he was on his horse.

00:15:12.943 --> 00:15:33.223
And his horse bridle, I've said this, it has beautiful jewels all throughout that bridle on that horse's bit going up through, and where he was holding the reins, it was beautiful—the jewels and the sapphires and the pearls and the diamonds and everything was on his bridle and what goes on the horse's chest.

00:15:36.996 --> 00:15:46.319
And he rode it up in the spirit realm, and I could see him riding on it, and his horse was beautiful white.

00:15:46.319 --> 00:15:50.240
It was a beautiful-looking, white-looking horse.

00:15:51.245 --> 00:15:54.259
It was gorgeous.

00:15:54.259 --> 00:15:55.264
It's absolutely gorgeous.

00:15:56.662 --> 00:16:01.360
And all the people, and you could see confetti in the air.

00:16:01.760 --> 00:16:23.029
Like confetti-like stuff was in the air, and how it was blowing at all times I have no idea because I don't know that celebration, but it was in the atmosphere, and it was on the streets, and it was being shaken like you'd see on New Year's Eve when the ball drops in Times Square and all the confetti is coming, but it was in the air, in the atmosphere.

00:16:23.029 --> 00:16:36.639
Colors and things were moving around as people were walking down, and they were blowing their horns and their trumpets, and they were sounding the praises of him, the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords.

00:16:36.639 --> 00:16:39.199
Beautiful.

00:16:39.199 --> 00:16:42.884
But the people were excited that we were coming home.

00:16:42.884 --> 00:16:52.320
All our loved ones that have gone on before us, that have passed on, ladies and gentlemen, to be absent from the body is to be present with the Lord.

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:54.240
And they are waiting for us.

00:16:54.240 --> 00:17:11.829
They are the great cloud of witnesses that are waiting on us, ladies and gentlemen, that are celebrating our soon return, that Jesus has paid the price for every single one of you to not go to hell.

00:17:11.829 --> 00:17:13.234
Thank you, Jesus.

00:17:13.234 --> 00:17:25.389
If you just accept him and turn from your sin and your wicked ways, Jesus has paid the price for every single one of you so you can go to heaven with him for eternity.

00:17:25.389 --> 00:17:30.382
I know a lot of you don't get it.

00:17:30.382 --> 00:17:51.703
There's a lot of you that are so lost, but I pray for you every day that the eyes of your understanding would be enlightened, that you would know the hope of your calling and how much he loves you, that he paid the price for every single one of you to walk in victory, going from glory to glory to glory.

00:17:57.144 --> 00:18:04.575
There was a stream, looked like a bridge, where the parade ended.

00:18:04.575 --> 00:18:16.537
It looked like it went a long way, but I could see the people, and they were lining both sides of the streets waiting for the people, like celebrating, getting ready for the people.

00:18:16.537 --> 00:18:25.280
And there was a bridge, the gold streets, the brick gold streets went over the bridge.

00:18:25.544 --> 00:18:27.655
And there was a stream going through there.

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:38.947
And then there was a massive castle that was right in front of it right here.

00:18:38.947 --> 00:18:45.350
A humongous, I'm talking ginormous-looking castle that was over here.

00:18:45.350 --> 00:18:50.400
Now, I don't know whose house that was, but they had big desires.

00:18:50.400 --> 00:18:56.700
Some people, if you only believe for small, you only get small because that was the desire of your heart.

00:18:56.700 --> 00:19:00.080
He's not going to override what you're believing for.

00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:03.182
What's your chokehold?

00:19:04.569 --> 00:19:09.760
How big is your faith and what you're believing for with God?

00:19:09.760 --> 00:19:16.140
God's limitless, but he will only move at your ability to believe him for it.

00:19:16.140 --> 00:19:21.280
Even in your heart's desires, he doesn't override you.

00:19:21.280 --> 00:19:23.433
You've got to stretch yourself.

00:19:23.433 --> 00:19:26.914
You've got to learn how to believe God for bigger.

00:19:26.914 --> 00:19:30.330
Some people have a measure of faith like the scripture.

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:35.120
Some people have a chokehold where you have to look at your chokehold.

00:19:35.511 --> 00:19:40.300
If I tell you to believe God for a million dollars, you say, "Ah, that's not a big deal.

00:19:40.300 --> 00:19:41.257
" Some people would say that.

00:19:41.257 --> 00:19:43.531
And some people go, "Oh my goodness, that's a lot of money.

00:19:43.531 --> 00:19:44.808
" Some people go, "That's not that big.

00:19:44.808 --> 00:19:51.800
" Then if I say you believe God for $10 million and then you go, "That's," and then somebody says, "That's not that bad.

00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:57.680
" And then somebody says, "I'm believing God for a hundred million dollars," and you go, "Woo, wow, $100 million.

00:19:57.680 --> 00:20:01.314
" That's what I'm trying to talk about: your choke point.

00:20:03.307 --> 00:20:13.280
Where does your faith go and you go, you know, where you go, "That's a lot," you know, versus "That's nothing"?

00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:18.720
Grow bigger in your capacity to believe God for more.

00:20:18.720 --> 00:20:27.960
Stretch your faith to believe him for exceedingly abundantly above all you dare ask or think, even in the next life.

00:20:27.960 --> 00:20:33.581
Some people, if you think like $1,000, you know, is a lot, you start out where your faith is $100.

00:20:42.297 --> 00:20:42.766
I can believe God for $100.

00:20:42.766 --> 00:20:45.320
So, you believe $100 ten times.

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:48.480
It doesn't make you less than.

00:20:48.480 --> 00:20:55.360
No, I'm just trying to tell you to stretch yourself because I saw houses that were beautiful.

00:21:05.848 --> 00:21:14.726
But I'm not running their house down in heaven by no means, because it makes anything on this earth look like a shack compared to a glorified house.

00:21:22.239 --> 00:21:22.519
But I'm just saying I could see massive castles.

00:21:22.519 --> 00:21:23.079
Wow.

00:21:23.079 --> 00:21:26.982
Somebody was believing for a massive castle and they got it.

00:21:26.982 --> 00:21:27.611
Wow.

00:21:30.231 --> 00:21:33.609
I don't know who it was, but I saw their house and I was like, "Are you kidding me?

00:21:34.150 --> 00:21:38.640
" That looked like a king's castle, but it wasn't where the Lord stayed.

00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:41.280
It was somebody's house.

00:21:44.620 --> 00:21:45.000
And this place was massive.

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:46.308
It was gorgeous.

00:21:46.308 --> 00:21:52.023
It looked like something out of Cinderella, you know, like a...

00:21:52.023 --> 00:22:01.039
But it was all looking like cobblestone again, you know, the cobblestone, but it was built like that all on the side of this hill.

00:22:01.725 --> 00:22:10.799
And I could see trees around it and some, like, not like, you know, like that peat moss, like moss stuff growing on it.

00:22:10.799 --> 00:22:15.539
Gorgeous looking like greenery and stuff around this castle.

00:22:18.809 --> 00:22:24.080
And it was on this hill above the golden street and it was over like over here from where they're having the parade.

00:22:24.080 --> 00:22:32.411
But it's just it's overwhelming how much he loves us and how much he's preparing a place for us.

00:22:32.799 --> 00:22:39.954
And our great cloud of witnesses, our loved ones, our relatives are watching and waiting for us.

00:22:42.560 --> 00:22:42.800
And Jesus Christ is coming, ladies and gentlemen.

00:22:50.702 --> 00:22:51.111
He's coming.

00:22:51.111 --> 00:22:52.820
Exciting!

00:23:09.119 --> 00:23:09.679
And we are going to be in paradise forever and ever and ever, singing praises to the King.

00:23:09.679 --> 00:23:14.849
It's a massive place, heaven is, and we will call it home.

00:23:15.470 --> 00:23:19.302
And he's going to make a new heaven and a new earth.

00:23:19.302 --> 00:23:35.760
